Crimes Committed by Lee Myung Bak Group during 100 Days of Their Office Brought to Light 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The National Reunification Institute made public a white paper Sunday disclosing the crimes committed by traitor Lee Myung Bak of south Korea for the past 100 days since the first day of his coming to power, talking about "lost decade." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The past 100 days of the conservative group's office are characterized by disgrace and crimes as it reduced south Korea to a complete colony of the U.S. and brought the north-south relations to collapse and made the dark clouds of confrontation and war hang over the Korean nation, the paper notes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citing facts to prove that Lee Myung Bak is the worst sycophantic traitor, the paper goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The traitor totally restored the humiliating master-servant relationship while talking about "tightened south Korea-U.S. alliance" quite contrary to the nation's desire for independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A particular mention should be made of the fact that during his junket to the U.S. in April he peddled "three principles for south Korea-U.S. alliance" such as "alliance based on value," "alliance based on confidence" and "peace-making alliance" and clang more tightly to the coattails of his American master, asserting that he would "upgrade south Korea-U.S. relationship to strategic alliance in the 21st century." (Yonhap News on April 16, 2008) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ulterior aim sought by the Lee Myung Bak group in working hard to quell the desire of the nation for independence was brought to light when he made desperate efforts to delay the transfer of the "rights to command wartime operations" from the U.S., talking about "damaged alliance", although the transfer is scheduled to be made by April 2012. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It even disclosed its intention to take an active part in the U.S.-led PSI and the Missile Defence System which even its preceding regimes hesitated to do. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No sooner had the traitor come to power than he staged large-scale Key Resolve and Foal Eagle joint military exercises after introducing U.S. imperialist aggression troops into south Korea and he is now contemplating hurling puppet forces' warships to the U.S.-led RIMPAC exercises for aggression slated to be staged in June. In February he held a "consultative meeting for the study of security" on Jeju Island by inviting there U.S. and Japanese military warhawks in a bid to knock into shape "triangular military alliance" for aggression. It adopted a "declaration" calling for establishing a triangular system for military cooperation and working out a joint military action plan and putting them into practice in "contingency." The Lee group also agreed to stage joint military exercises involving the U.S., Japan and south Korea from June. (Choongang Ilbo on February 20, 2008) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lee Myung Bak reduced south Korea into a total colony of the U.S. in the economic field, too. Soon after his coming to power he went busy with the moves to conclude the south Korea-U.S. FTA and totally opened south Korea's market to American beef, thus committing such treachery as allowing American beef fraught with the danger of mad cow disease to find its way to south Korean market unhindered. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lee also worked hard to Americanize south Korea's culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No sooner had Lee seized power than he proposed the "plan for intensified English education" unprecedented in history which calls for banning the use of Korean language but allowing the use of English only in school education from primary schools and adopted it as a policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went the lengths of describing the actions taken by the ancestors to set fire to the U.S. pirate ship "General Sherman" and send it to the bottom of the river and their erection of "monuments to repelling aggressors' invasions" in different parts of Korea as a "big blunder" and raving that "such trouble should never be allowed to repeat itself." He even made the gesture of granting Korean names to U.S. ambassadors and brasshats of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces before their assumption of office in south Korea. He was so insane as to name a general of the U.S. forces in south Korea "Ulji," surname of a famous patriotic commander of Korea, shortly ago. (Yonhap News on May 22, 2008) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lee Myung Bak formed the "government" with pro-U.S. stooges and even appointed foreigners including American as policy advisers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This traitor even blustered that he would let even a foreigner hold the ministerial post if necessary in the future. (Yonhap News on April 9, 2008) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He is holding Japan as dear as his ancestral tablet, keeping mum about the crimes committed by it in the past under the watchword of "new era of cooperation" and "future-oriented conception." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The white paper also cites facts to prove that Lee pushed the north-south relations to catastrophe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The traitor negated the June 15 joint declaration, a great programme for national reunification in the new century, and the October 4 declaration, a programme for putting the joint declaration into practice, and stood in the way of their implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even before coming to power the traitor took issue with the above-said declarations, terming them "theory-like" and "abstract." As soon as he was elected "president" he openly negated what the preceding "government" agreed with the north, raving that the "new government" has no obligation to implement them." (Dong-A Ilbo on February 2, 2008) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group slashed every paragraph of the above-said declarations, putting up "pragmatism" as a slogan for its rule. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He opposed the first paragraph of the October 4 declaration, claiming that implementing it is little short of setting June 15 as a "national holiday" and accepting the federal formula. As for the paragraphs dealing with the north-south relations, he opposed them, asserting they are aimed to have the "National Security Law" repealed. As far as the paragraphs dealing with peace are concerned, he rejected them, claiming that they seek "the neutralization of the northern limit line" and "they are likely to cause a problem to security." And when referring to the paragraphs dealing with economic cooperation, he insisted he cannot accept them as they are tantamount to "a drain on resources under the pretext of economic cooperation." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The true aim sought by the Lee group in touting "no nukes, opening and 3,000 dollars" as "a policy toward the north" is to negate the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration and break the north-south relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group slandered the idea of "By our nation itself" clarified in the June 15 joint declaration as "narrow-minded nationalism" and "exclusionist nationalism." They are working hard to justify "no nukes, opening and 3,000 dollars" and getting noisier in the "nuclear racket" and "human rights row" against the DPRK, crying out for "open nationalism." This is nothing but a revelation of their intention to scrap the June 15 joint declaration and bring the inter-Korean relations to collapse. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group has deliberately evaded the commitments stipulated in the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has harshly persecuted and suppressed people of different social standings involved in the reunification movement in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its moves to incite confrontation with the DPRK found their vivid expression in letting loose bellicose outbursts against the DPRK and stepping up the preparations for a war of aggression against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Of late this group proposed the "resumption of dialogue" and the setting up of "south-north liaison offices". But this is nothing but a ridiculous ploy to hoodwink the public opinion and evade the responsibility for bedeviling the north-south relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The paper also lashed out at the Lee group for reducing south Korea to a dark land under the fascist dictatorship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This group has directed all efforts to establishing undemocratic fascist dictatorship and has not bothered to purge anyone they deemed standing in the way of doing so even a bit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This group has also become all the more frantic in suppressing political opponents and progressive forces involving people of various social strata. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Not a few politicians including those who ran for presidency as candidates from ruling and opposition parties have been subject to the persecution and investigation by fascist prosecution after becoming targets of political reprisal by Lee. There appeared again riot police equipped with cushion helmet, shield and electric shock devices as well as water cannons and "Paekgoldan" which earned ill-fame during the fascist regime in the past. The "summary trial system" calling for punishing the accused without going through the procedures of public trial was restored in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group's fascist true nature found a vivid manifestation in their brutal suppression of the wide-spread struggle waged by people from all walks of life in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This group malignantly slandered even the heroic popular resistances waged by south Koreans in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A typical example of this is that the "New Right Textbooks Forum", a political force backing the traitorous group, published a textbook in March describing traitor Park Chung Hee's "May 16 military coup" as a "revolution" and distorting and downplaying the movement for democratization waged by south Koreans from all walks of life including the April 19 popular uprising and the May 18 popular uprising. (Thongil News on April 24, 2008) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All what has happened in south Korea are awful consequences and tragic product of treacherous "pragmatism" advocated by Lee Myung Bak. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The conservative group of south Korea is now making desperate efforts to prolong its dirty remaining days but with nothing can it stem the trend of the times and the desire of the nation for independence, democracy and reunification, concludes the paper.

Greetings to Italian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Monday sent a message of greetings to President of Italy Giorgio Napolitano on the occasion of its national day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim in the message wished the Italian people progress and prosperity, expressing the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would continue to grow stronger in the future, too.

DPRK Women's Football Team Defeats Its Chinese Rival 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The DPRK women's football team beat its Chinese rival 1:0 in a league match of Group A for the 2008 Asian Women's Football Championship on June 1, thus coming first in the group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It advanced into semi-finals.

Great Songun Politics Admired by World 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The Songun idea and Songun politics of the DPRK is admired as the banner of independence against imperialism and the symbol of victory, gripping the hearts of the progressives worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An extensive work is in progress in diverse forms and ways on a global scale to introduce and propagate them and organizations for the study of Songun politics are expanded and strengthened. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Groups for the study of Songun politics have been formed in various countries such as Peru, the UK, the U.S., Ukraine and Chile and they are growing in number every year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 International and regional conferences and national forums and public presentations of study results on the Songun idea and Songun politics are held in succession. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Symposiums and lectures, discussions and other meetings on the theme of the Songun idea and Songun politics took place on several hundred occasions in more than 70 countries in Juche 92(2003) and in over 120 countries and regions in 2006. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The year 2007 witnessed a total of 600-odd versatile functions on the Songun idea and Songun politics in upwards of 130 countries including Laos, India, France and Bulgaria and regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fast spread of the Songun idea and Songun politics is well illustrated by the fact that media of over 100 countries around the world have dealt with the Songun idea and Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The progressive people of the world highly appraise the Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il as most superior and powerful one to meet the independent demand of the popular masses, defend the dignity of the country and the nation and promote the building of an independent new world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics in his article earnestly praised the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il, saying the world progressives owe much to him, to his Songun politics.

Sangphal Ponds on Mt. Kumgang 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- There are the Sangphal Ponds on Mt. Kumgang of Korea, a mountain famous in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Wonderful is the scenery around the ponds for the crystal-clear water flowing into them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The area around the ponds is an unsplit rock where eight round ponds came into being in a row, washed by water from time immemorial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Water flows into the ponds in turn and forms magnificent waterfalls, falling down from a precipice via the last pond and narrow rock groove. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
This is the Kuryong Falls, one of the three famous falls in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
There are stiff cliffs on both sides of the pond valley where pine-nut, maple and other trees grow in rock cracks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The trees spread wonderful scenery, harmonized with the ponds, cliffs and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
There is the legend "Eight Fairies of Mt. Kumgang" which tells that eight fairies ascended to heaven after bathing in the Sangphal Ponds.

Lee Myung Bak Group's Sinister Attempt Flayed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification of south Korea called a press conference outside the building of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade in Seoul on May 29 to denounce the Lee Myung Bak group's sinister scheme. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the conference speakers noted that traitor Lee Myung Bak sent a delegation to a "meeting" related to the PSI to be held in the United States. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They contended that if his group materializes the involvement of south Korea in the PSI at any cost, calling for priority to "restoration of alliance" with the U.S., it would pose a serious danger to peace on the Korean Peninsula and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also charged that this would add fuel to the realization of the U.S. strategy for supremacy as well as such plans for aggression on the DPRK as "OPLAN 5029." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the authorities' behavior will only scuttle the inter-Korean relations, they held that if the Lee group truly wants to follow the trend of the times, it should come out for implementing the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration, far from kowtowing to the outsiders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that the participation in the PSI is illegal as it is contrary not only to the interests of the people but peace and reunification of the Korean Peninsula and in contravention of international law.

Conservative Media's Distorted Reports Denounced in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The People's Measure Council against the Total Opening of south Korean Market to American Beef called a press conference outside the Chosun Ilbo in Seoul on May 28 to denounce the conservative media for their distorted reports. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the conference speakers charged that such conservative media as Chosun Ilbo, Choongang Ilbo and Dong-A Ilbo have described the citizens' voluntary candlelight demonstrations as movement "sponsored by wire-pulling force", terming the struggle against the import of American beef "illegal." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Contending that with the conservative media left intact, it is impossible to achieve democracy in south Korea, they warned that the conservative media, patronized by the dictatorial regimes in the past, would be bound to face the punishment by the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the conference the council declared that it would totally refuse the conservative media's coverage of candlelight demos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the conference, the organization, together with citizens, conducted information activities critical of the conservative media in front of the Dong-A Ilbo.

188th Anti-U.S. Friday Rally Held in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration and other civic and social organizations of south Korea held the 188th Friday rally for opposing the U.S. and war and demanding the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from south Korea outside the U.S. embassy in Seoul on May 23. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution, read out at the rally, referred to the fact that the U.S. ambassador in Seoul openly blackmailed the representative of a south Korean opposition party standing against the import of American beef. This was an undisguised intervention in politics and interference in internal affairs, it pointed out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ambassador has become a target of the south Korean people's criticism as he slandered the DPRK and hindered the reconciliation and cooperation of the Korean nation while interfering in south Korea's internal affairs just after he proceeded to his post, the resolution noted, and said: The present reality makes the south Korean people fully realize once again that south Korea is a colony of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution demanded that the U.S. ambassador apologize to the south Korean people and immediately quit south Korea and that the Lee Myung Bak group reject the U.S. pressure for south Korea's import of American beef and come out to the renegotiations on it as soon as possible.

Large-scale Anti-"Government" Struggle Waged in Seoul
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- A large-scale anti-"government" struggle was waged in Seoul on May 31 in protest against the Lee Myung Bak group's moves to open south Korean market to American beef. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was participated in by members of civic and public organizations including the People's Measure Council against the Total Opening of south Korean Market to American Beef and workers, peasants and students from across south Korea, at least 100,000 in all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Read out at a candlelight rally held in University Street was an "appeal to the people" issued by the above-said council. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal said that the candlelight actions of different circles to check the import of American beef fraught with the danger of "mad cow disease" are historic resistance to protect the lives of the people and bring down the Lee Myung Bak regime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Urging the people to launch a one million-strong candlelight action on the occasion of the anniversary of the June resistance against the dictatorial regime, the appeal called for making angry people's candlelight actions sweep all parts of south Korea and protecting their sovereignty through a large-scale candlelight march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the rally speakers accused the Lee Myung Bak "government" of branding the candlelight actions as "riots," paying no heed to the people's protest against the import of beef, and called for escalating the candlelight actions against the import of beef into anti-"government" resistance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally the participants staged a demonstration towards "Chongwadae".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Democratic Labor Party called a press conference at Chonggye Square where its leadership was on a hunger sit-in strike and demanded the retraction of the "official instructions" issued by the Lee Myung Bak group on the hygienic conditions for the beef import. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Democratic Party for Unity formed the headquarters for implementing measures for renegotiations on beef import and expressed its will to solidarize with the candlelight actions. "National assemblymen" from the party took part in a candlelight rally and demonstration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar rallies and demonstrations took place in Kwangju, Ulsan, Taegu and other areas of south Korea simultaneously.

Crackdown upon Candlelight Rallies Protested in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The Youth and Students Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration of south Korea released a statement on May 25 in protest against the Lee Myung Bak group's reckless suppression of the participants in candlelight actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The number of cases of arrests of participants of candlelight rallies against the import of American beef is on the steady increase in south Korea and conservative media and the group of the Grand National Party of south Korea are getting evermore pronounced in their moves to mislead the public opinion, the statement noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The prevailing situation goes to prove that the traitorous clique are little different from the gang of fascist dictators in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should clearly know that suppression is not a cure-all. People's candlelight actions for defending the right to existence will go on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the General Students Council of University of Agriculture of south Korea called a press conference on May 27 before launching a hunger sit-in in protest against the action taken by the university side to deter students from participating in candlelight rallies.

Lee Myung Bak Group's Human Rights Abuses Denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- Amnesty International in a recent annual report denounced the Lee Myung Bak group for perpetrating such human rights abuses as brutally cracking down upon south Korean people's struggle against the opening of south Korean markets to American beef, according to CBS of south Korea on May 28. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amnesty International accused the south Korean authorities of largely abridging the "freedom of expression including assembly and demonstration." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is part of human rights abuses for the police to take legal actions against the participants of the candlelight rallies now under way across south Korea everyday in protest against the import of American beef by branding them as "illegal," it noted.

S. Koreans' Anti-"Government" Struggle Supported in Britain
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The British Association for the Study of Songun Policy and the British Group for the Study of the Juche Idea released a joint statement on May 19 in support of the south Korean people's struggle against the authorities' moves to import American beef. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement charged that the total opening of south Korean market to American beef is a reckless anti-popular policy of the Lee Myung Bak puppet authorities who are making south Korea more dependent upon foreign forces and wholly ruining the existence of stockbreeding households and driving them to misery, poverty and unemployment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement expressed full support for the south Korean people in their struggle against the import of American beef and called upon all the progressive organizations to conduct brisk solidarity activities for supporting their struggle.

Kim Jong Il dirige sobre terreno Fundicion de Hungnam
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 2 de junio (ATCC) -- El Dirigente  Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, dirigio sobre el terreno la Fundicion de Metales No Ferrosos de Hungnam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Guiado por los funcionarios directivos de la empresa, el Dirigente recorrio la sala para educacion en los materiales de la historia revolucionaria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Recordo con profunda emocion el glorioso proceso del desarrollo de la empresa que gracias al Presidente Kim Il Sung ha venido recorriendo por un camino de prosperidad y dijo que bajo su sabia direccion y su minucioso cuidado la empresa se ha convertido en una fidedigna base productiva de metales no ferrosos del pais y apunto que las inmortales hazanas revolucionarias del Presidente quedaran eternamente en los anales de la patria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al recorrer el taller de aleacion dura, el horno de fusion y otros procesos productivos, se entero de detalles del estado de reconstruccion tecnica y de produccion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente expreso una gran satisfaccion de que los funcionarios, obreros y tecnicos de la Fundicion terminaron magnificamente en un corto espacio de tiempo la dificil y enorme obra de reconstruccion apoyandose en sus propias fuerzas y tecnicas y evaluo altamente sus meritos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Se  mostro alegre de que los tecnicos y obreros de la Fundicion solucionaron por cuenta propia muchos problemas cientifico-tecnicos y subrayo que cuando se pongan de pleno manifiesto el estilo de lucha y el espiritu revolucionario de autoconfianza que exige  investigar y crear lo nuevo con sus propias fuerzas y talentos, sera posible hacer pensamientos originales e invenciones innovadoras y abrir el especifico dominio cientifico y tecnico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente presento las tareas que se presentan ante la empresa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Dijo que la tarea importantisima de la Fundicion es normalizar en alto nivel la produccion y, al mismo tiempo, poner todos los procesos productivos sobre la base cientifico-tecnica mas alta concentrando de continuo las fuerzas en la labor de reconstruccion tecnica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Indico que la empresa debe desarrollar animadamente el movimiento masivo de innovacion tecnica, introducir sin cesar nuevas tecnicas para aumentar las variedades de los metales no ferrosos y raros y recoger completamente los metales valiosos elevando la  tasa de rendimiento de la fundicion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para poner en pleno funcionamiento la Fundicion de Metales No Ferrosos de Hungnam es preciso que las minas relacionadas envien con suficiencia los minerales concentrados de buena calidad, senalo y continuo que para este fin deben incrementar mas la produccion en las minas y tomar las medidas estrictas para transportar a tiempo los minerales enriquecidos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al recorrer las instalaciones de intendencia se entero del estado del servicio de abastecimiento para los obreros. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Expreso gran satisfaccion de que los funcionarios de la empresa, con el correcto punto de vista a la labor de intendencia, se esfuerzan con teson por ofrecer excelentes condiciones de vida alimentaria a los obreros y los elogio por sus esfuerzos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Enfatizo que todas las fabricas y empresas deben prestar primordial atencion a esta labor y ofrecer las mejores condiciones de vida a los obreros. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Manifesto su conviccion de que los funcionarios, obreros y tecnicos de la Fundicion cumpliran con exito las tareas revolucionarias presentadas ante la empresa y responderan a la elevada confianza y expectativa del partido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le acompanaron Kim Ki Nam y Pak Nam Gi, secretario y jefe de departamento, del CC del PTC, respectivamente.

IRP analiza crimenes de Lee Myung Bak en 100 dias de su gobernacion
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 2 de junio (ATCC) -- El Instituto de Reunificacion de la Patria (IRP) hizo publica la vispera una carta blanca revelando los actos criminales que cometio el traidor Lee Myung Bak durante 100 dias desde su llegada al poder jurando compensar los supuestos "10 anos perdidos".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El documento destaca que esos 100 dias posteriores a la toma del poder por la banda de conservadores liderados por Lee son el periodo de verguenzas y crimenes en que el Sur de Corea se hizo la peor colonia de EE.UU.,  entraron en la fase de ruptura las relaciones Norte-Sur y se cernio el nubarron de confrontacion y guerra sobre la nacion coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Desenmascara con datos que el traidor Lee Myung Bak es el vendepatria y servil a grandes potencias sin precedente en la historia y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En contraste con la aspiracion independiente de la nacion, Lee recupero totalmente las humillantes relaciones dependientes de EE.UU. abogando por el "fortalecimiento de la alianza" con este imperio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante la visita a EE.UU. realizada en abril, dijo que "hara de las relaciones Sur de Corea-EE.UU. las de alianza estrategica del siglo XXI" y se acerco mas a su amo gringo proponiendo los "tres principios de la alianza Sur de Corea-EE.UU.", o sea, el "valor", la "confianza" y el "establecimiento de paz".(Versiones de Yonhap News del 16 de abril de 2008) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La naturaleza de la banda de Lee desafiante a la aspiracion independiente de la nacion se muestra patentemente en sus desesperadas maniobras para dilatar el recibo del "mando de operaciones en el tiempo de guerra", que EE.UU. debe entregar al Sur de Corea hasta abril de 2012,  pretextando que esto "afectara las relaciones de alianza".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para colmo, el "poder" de Lee exteriorizo el intento de tomar parte activa hasta en la "Iniciativa de Seguridad contra la Proliferacion" (PSI en ingles) y el Sistema Antimisiles bajo el liderazgo de EE.UU., a lo cual no se atrevieron los "regimenes" anteriores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tan pronto como tomo el "poder", el traidor Lee desarrollo los ejercicios militares conjuntos de gran envergadura "Key Resolve" y "Aguilucho" con colosales efectivos norteamericanos arribados al suelo surcoreano y proyecta enviar los buques de guerra del ejercito titere surcoreano al agresivo ejercicio "Rimpac" que se realizara en junio bajo la direccion de EE.UU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al pretender el establecimiento de la agresiva "alianza militar tripartita" realizo en febrero de este ano en la isla Jeju la "reunion consultiva de estudio de seguridad" con las figuras belicistas de los circulos militares de EE.UU. y Japon. En esa ocasion, se publico la "declaracion" de que las 3 partes entran en la accion practica luego de establecer el sistema de cooperacion militar y elaborar el plan de acciones militares conjuntas entre si para el "tiempo de emergencia" y se acordo desplegar desde junio los ejercicios militares tripartitas.(Edicion del 20 de febrero de 2008 de Choongang Ilbo) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El traidor Lee convirtio el Sur de Corea en la peor colonia de EE.UU. tambien en el plano economico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En cuanto llego al "poder" se esforzo locamente por la firma del "Tratado de Libre Comercio" con EE.UU. y no vacilo en abrir totalmente el mercado domestico a la carne de res norteamericana sospechosa de la "enfermedad de vacas locas".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Igualmente, maniobro para americanizar en sentido cultural el Sur de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Desde el comienzo de su mandato, refrendo en una politica el "proyecto del fortalecimiento de la ensenanza de ingles" sin precedente en la historia, segun el cual en la educacion escolar desde en la escuela primaria se prohibe el uso del idioma coreano y se permite unicamente el ingles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al calificar de gran error el hundimiento del barco agresor norteamericano "Sherman" y la construccion por doquier de las "lapidas de rechazamiento a la reconciliacion con el invasor" por los antepasados, Lee dice que "no debemos volver a cometer tal error". Ademas, al cabo de dar nombres coreanos a los embajadores norteamericanos y las cabecillas de las tropas norteamericanas en el Sur de Corea, hace poco, cometio la locura de apellidar a un general de las tropas norteamericanas ocupantes del Sur de Corea con "Ulji", apellido de un celebre general patriotico de Corea.(Versiones del 22 de mayo de 2008 de Yonhap News) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Lee compuso su equipo del "poder" con los lacayos proyanquis y designo como asesores de politica hasta a los extranjeros incluso los norteamericanos.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Dice que en caso necesario, nombraria al extranjero incluso en el cargo de ministro.(Versiones del 9 de abril de 2008 de Yonhap News) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al hablar de la "nueva epoca de cooperacion" y la "aspiracion al futuro", Lee respeta tambien a Japon como a su abuelo sin cuestionar los crimenes cometidos en el pasado por este pais isleno. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La banda de Lee llevo a la catastrofe las relaciones con el Norte. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El traidor Lee Myung Bak nego la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio, gran programa de la reunificacion de la patria del nuevo siglo, y la Declaracion del 4 de Octubre, programa para la implementacion de la primera. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ya desde antes de tomar el "poder", el habia censurado esas declaraciones calificandolas de "teoricas" y "abstractas".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Despues de ocupar la "presidencia", las nego abiertamente diciendo que el nuevo "regimen" "no tiene deber de ejecutar" lo acordado por los antecesores.(Edicion del 2 de febrero de 2008 del periodico Dong-A Ilbo) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al presentar el "pragmatismo" como consigna de dominacion, la banda de Lee invalido arbitrariamente las declaraciones arriba mencionadas letra por letra y articulo por articulo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En particular, se opuso al primer articulo de la Declaracion del 4 de Octubre diciendo que este instituye el 15 de Junio como "dia de la fundacion del pais" y acepta el sistema federal y rehuso el articulo de las relaciones Norte-Sur senalando que esto pretende abolir la "ley de seguridad". Hizo lo mismo con los articulos de la paz y de la cooperacion economica bajo pretexto de la "nulidad de la linea de limite al Norte", "problema de seguridad" y "asistencia desmesurada disfrazada de colaboracion economica".(versiones del 7 de octubre de 2007 de Pressian) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
La banda de Lee sale con la teoria de "desnuclearizacion, apertura y 3,000 dolares" como "politica con respecto al Norte de Corea". Pero, su designio fundamental redunda en negar la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio y la Declaracion de 4 de Octubre y romper las relaciones Norte-Sur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esta banda insulto hasta el ideal de "Entre nosotros, los connacionales" dilucidado en la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio como el "nacionalismo estrecho" y "nacionalismo chovinista" y dijo que hay que materializar el "nacionalismo abierto" justificando asi la teoria de "desnuclearizacion, apertura y 3,000 dolares" y se aferra mas en el "alboroto nuclear" y " el de derechos humanos". Esto no es nada mas que la sofisteria de invalidar el 15 de junio y llevar al fracaso las relaciones Norte-Sur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La banda de Lee se opone intencionalmente a la ejecucion de la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio y la Declaracion del 4 de Octubre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La mencionada banda acosa y reprime cruelmente el movimiento de distintos estratos del Sur de Corea por la reunificacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Las maniobras de confrontacion anti-RPDC de la banda de Lee se exponen de modo mas concentrado en lanzar arbitrariamente palabrotas belicosas contra la RPDC y dar acicate a los preparativos de la guerra de agresion al Norte de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aunque en los ultimos dias la bandada de Lee hable de la "reanudacion del dialogo", la "instalacion de la oficina de enlace Sur-Norte" y otras cosas, esto no pasa de ser un ardid ridiculo para enganar la opinion publica y librarse de la responsabilidad de haber llevado al fracaso las relaciones Norte-Sur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La carta blanca pone al desnudo el crimen de que la banda de Lee convirtio el Sur de Corea en un infierno donde reinan el fascismo y la dictadura. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La camarilla de Lee dedico toda la fuerza al establecimiento del sistema de dictadura fascista contra la democracia y no titubeo en eliminar todo lo que obstaculiza al respecto. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ademas recurre con frenesi a la represion contra sus rivales politicos y las fuerzas progresistas de distintos estratos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Muchas personalidades politicas incluyendo los candidatos de los partidos en poder y oposicion durante el periodo de las "elecciones presidenciales" se convirtieron en objetos de represalia politica de Lee y se vieron obligadas a la persecucion de la fiscalia fascista y aparecieron otra vez los policias represivos armados totalmente con los cascos, escudos e impactor electrico, canones de agua y "Paekgoldan" que exaltaron su infamia en el anterior "poder" fascista y resucito el "sistema de sentencia inmediata" que castiga sin procedimiento de juicio a los aprisionados. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La naturaleza fascista de la banda de Lee se revela concentradamente en que ultimamente en el Sur de Corea se reprime salvajemente la lucha de los habitantes de distintos estratos que se libra ampliamente en el Sur de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ella calumnia e insulta siniestramente la sublevacion popular heroica de los habitantes surcoreanos del tiempo pasado. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Por ejemplo, el pasado mes de marzo el "Foro de manual New Right" que es fuerza de apoyo politico de la banda traidora publico el manual del contenido de que califico positivamente de una "revolucion" el "golpe militar del 16 de mayo" desatado por el traidor Pak Chung Hee, tergiversa y calumnia el significado del movimiento por la democratizacion de distintos sectores del Sur de Corea inclusive el de 19 de abril y el de 18 de mayo.("Thong-il News" 24 de abril de 2008) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La carta blanca denuncia que la realidad dada en el Sur de Corea es la triste consecuencia y el resultado tragico que dio el "pragmatismo" antinacional del traidor Lee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aunque la banda conservadora del Sur de Corea haga esfuerzos desesperados por mantener su sucia vida es imposible detener con nada la tendencia de la epoca y la aspiracion de la nacion hacia la independencia, la democracia y la reunificacion.

Equipo coreano de futbol femenino llega a la semifinal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 2 de junio (ATCC) -- El equipo coreano gano por 1 a 0 a la seleccion china en el partido que tuvo lugar el dia primero como parte de los encuentros del grupo A del torneo de liga por grupos del Campeonato Asiatico de Futbol Femenino 2008. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi el once coreano llego a la semifinal como primer lugar de su grupo.
